  "text": "Other approaches to ground state molecular cooling of molecular ions include using ultra-cold atoms for sympathetic cooling [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , or simply building the ion trap in a cryostat. Cryogenic ion traps are not a new idea (26 ) but recent developments in trap fabrication processes have meant that their use seems likely to become more widespread over the next few years. Indeed cryogenic ion traps are currently under development in a number of laboratories worldwide (27 ) 17 .",
